    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix unexpected behavior in itti_subscribe_event_fd due to missing headers and incorrect epoll event setup\n\n### Summary\nWhen calling itti_subscribe_event_fd() the behavior is not what is expected. This is caused by missing system headers and incorrect epoll event data initialization.\n\nThe function was using errno and strerror() without including errno.h and string.h, which could lead to undefined behavior. Additionally, it was setting both event.data.u64 and event.data.fd in the epoll event structure, which could cause issues depending on system architecture.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/ocp_itti/intertask_interface.cpp`: Added missing errno.h and string.h headers for proper errno and strerror() support. Removed redundant event.data.u64 = 0 assignment, keeping only the correct event.data.fd = fd initialization.\n\n### Reproduction\nUsers may observe that file descriptors passed to itti_subscribe_event_fd() are not properly monitored for events, or that error handling in the function doesn't work as expected. In some cases, this could lead to epoll not correctly notifying tasks when data is available on subscribed file descriptors.\n"
}